Insider tip: Because of its natural attractions and high altitude, make sure that the timing of your visit is perfect. Unless you’re going to snowboard or ski, try to avoid the winter months and opt for the spring and summer season when roads are easier to access.

📍Kyrgyzstan

🇰🇬 #discoverKyrgyzstan with @albertdrosphotography

Autumn walks in Finland 🍁✨ Have you seen Finland in the fall season before?

Autumn leaf colours, also known as ""Ruska"" to locals, characterises the autumn months in Finland. The country’s landscapes are painted in vivid yellows, reds and browns, making every walk and hike even more magical. Would you visit Finland during this season?

📍Finland

🇫🇮 #discoverFinland with @jukkarisikko

Nature’s wonders 🤯 Located along the floor of the Atlantic Ocean, the Mid-Atlantic Ridge is the most extensive chain of mountains of earth, but less than 10% of the range is actually visible for us. There are very few places where the range isn’t hidden, and Iceland is one of the only places where you can see and even stand on this breathtaking ridge. Would you visit this area?

📍 Iceland

🇮🇸 #discoverIceland with @zynl_ozturk
Video by Cografya Dünyası on YouTube
via @geomorphological_landscapes

node.text:
Real life fairytale village 🌿 Would you visit Lauterbrunnen?

This picturesque village is located in the Swiss alps. Fringed by rocky cliffs, vibrant greens and waterfalls, this spot is one of the most impressive valleys of the area. ⛰️

Insider tip: Although it’s mostly known as an expansive skiing spot during winter, Lauterbrunnen is just as pretty during summer (and it’s perfect for hiking!).

📍Lauterbrunnen, Switzerland

🇨🇭 #discoverSwitzerland with @thetravelergene

Pure magic ✨📚 You can find this surreal bookstore in  Dujiangyan Zhongshuge, located in Chengdu, China. This two-story bookstore was designed by architecture firm X+Living, and is a true wonderland for book lovers. C-shaped bookshelves and mirrored ceilings give off an extended, almost never-ending illusion. Would you spend the day here?

📍Dujiangyan Zhongshuge, China

🇨🇳 #discoverChina with @xlivingart

Phyllium giganteum lifecycle with @insecthaus_adi 🍃

Phyllium giganteum is a very wide and large leaf insect with a body shaped like a leaf. Also the legs have appendages making it look like leaves. In nature it can be found in tropical forests in Malaysia. This species consists of only females.

#discoverearth with @insecthaus_adi
